Project Summary: Diwali Sales Data Analysis
This project focuses on analyzing customer purchasing behavior during the Diwali season using a retail dataset. The objective was to extract actionable insights about buyers, their preferences, and sales trends.

âœ… Key Steps:
Data Cleaning & Preparation:

Removed irrelevant columns and missing values

Converted necessary data types for analysis

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA):

Performed using Seaborn & Matplotlib for visual insights

Grouped and compared data by demographic and purchase features

ğŸ” Major Insights:
Gender: Females made more purchases and contributed more to total sales than males.

Age Group: The 26â€“35 age group showed the highest buying activity, especially among females.

State: Most orders and revenue came from Uttar Pradesh, Maharashtra, and Karnataka.

Marital Status: Married women were the largest contributors to overall sales.

Occupation: Customers in IT, Healthcare, and Aviation sectors were the top spenders.

Product Categories: Food, Clothing, and Electronics were the most purchased product types.

Top Products: Specific product IDs emerged as the best-sellers by volume.

ğŸ‘¥ Customer Persona Identified:
Married women aged 26â€“35 from UP, Maharashtra, or Karnataka, working in IT, Healthcare, or Aviation, primarily shopping for Food, Clothing, and Electronics.

ğŸ¯ Conclusion:
The analysis reveals clear demographic patterns and purchasing behaviors, helping businesses target high-value customer segments more effectively. 
This insight can be used to improve marketing, inventory planning, and sales strategies for future festive seasons.








